<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="324" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[135,763,1220,1978]" lastBlockId="11.[825,1452,137,193]" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">
The familial delimitation of 
<taxonomicName box="[522,690,1252,1276]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinonycteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Rhinonycteridae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lydekker, in Flower and Lydekker" authorityYear="1891" box="[135,290,1284,1308]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Hipposideridae</taxonomicName>
results in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[418,483,1284,1308]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Asellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[418,483,1284,1308]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Asellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being basal to all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lydekker, in Flower and Lydekker" authorityYear="1891" box="[135,292,1316,1340]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Hipposideridae</taxonomicName>
. This clade received strong bootstrap and PP support across all analyses (see supplementary 
<tableCitation box="[668,758,1348,1372]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="7.[135,187,1476,1496]" captionText="Table 2. P Values Resulting from Statistical Comparison of Alternative Phylogenetic Hypotheses Using Topology Tests in Tree Puzzle and Consel." pageId="11" pageNumber="324">table S2</tableCitation>
, Supplementary Material online). This is contrary to a previous study, which, based on morphological data, places 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1941" box="[669,762,1412,1436]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Aselliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[669,762,1412,1436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Aselliscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
basal (
<bibRefCitation author="Hand S &amp; Kirsch J." box="[201,429,1444,1468]" editor="Kunz TH &amp; Racey PA" journalOrPublisher="Washington (DC): Smithsonian Institution Press" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" pagination="72 - 90" refId="ref16407" refString="Hand S, Kirsch J. 1998. A southern origin for the Hipposideridae (Microchiroptera)? Evidence from the Australian fossil record. In: Kunz TH, Racey PA, editors. Bat biology and conservation. Washington (DC): Smithsonian Institution Press. p. 72 - 90." title="A southern origin for the Hipposideridae (Microchiroptera)? Evidence from the Australian fossil record" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Bat biology and conservation" year="1998">Hand and Kirsch 1998</bibRefCitation>
), despite the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[696,761,1444,1468]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Asellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[696,761,1444,1468]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Asellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in their data set. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1941" box="[437,530,1476,1500]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Aselliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[437,530,1476,1500]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Aselliscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains two species, and its placement in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lydekker, in Flower and Lydekker" authorityYear="1891" box="[395,550,1508,1532]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Hipposideridae</taxonomicName>
phylogeny has been controversial. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pierson ED" box="[283,435,1540,1564]" journalOrPublisher="University of California, Berkeley, USA" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" refId="ref17977" refString="Pierson ED 1986. Molecular systematics of the Microchiroptera: higher taxon relationships and biogeography. PhD dissertation. University of California, Berkeley, USA." title="Molecular systematics of the Microchiroptera: higher taxon relationships and biogeography" type="book" year="1986">Pierson (1986)</bibRefCitation>
concluded that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1941" box="[619,712,1540,1564]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Aselliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[619,712,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Aselliscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not a member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lydekker, in Flower and Lydekker" authorityYear="1891" box="[349,504,1571,1595]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Hipposideridae</taxonomicName>
and was more closely aligned with the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[327,479,1603,1627]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Rhinolophidae</taxonomicName>
, based on immunological transferrin distance data. Morphological data place this genus among other 
<taxonomicName box="[365,494,1667,1691]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[365,494,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Hipposideros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<bibRefCitation author="Bogdanowicz W &amp; Owen R." editor="Kunz TH &amp; Racey PA" journalOrPublisher="Bat biology and conservation. Washington (DC): Smithsonian Institution Press" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" pagination="27 - 42" refId="ref15487" refString="Bogdanowicz W, Owen R. 1998. In the Minotaurs labyrinth: phylogeny of the bat family Hipposideridae. In: Kunz TH, Racey PA, editors. Bat biology and conservation. Washington (DC): Smithsonian Institution Press. p. 27 - 42." type="book chapter" volumeTitle="the Minotaurs labyrinth: phylogeny of the bat family Hipposideridae. In" year="1998">Bogdanowicz and Owen 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hand S &amp; Kirsch J." box="[274,517,1699,1723]" editor="Kunz TH &amp; Racey PA" journalOrPublisher="Washington (DC): Smithsonian Institution Press" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" pagination="72 - 90" refId="ref16407" refString="Hand S, Kirsch J. 1998. A southern origin for the Hipposideridae (Microchiroptera)? Evidence from the Australian fossil record. In: Kunz TH, Racey PA, editors. Bat biology and conservation. Washington (DC): Smithsonian Institution Press. p. 72 - 90." title="A southern origin for the Hipposideridae (Microchiroptera)? Evidence from the Australian fossil record" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Bat biology and conservation" year="1998">Hand and Kirsch 1998</bibRefCitation>
). These morphological results are in agreement with molecular data, which found strong support for a sister taxa relationship between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1941" box="[669,762,1763,1787]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Aselliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[669,762,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Aselliscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Li et al. 2007)" baseAuthorityName="Li" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[186,439,1795,1819]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Coelops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[186,263,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Coelops</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Li G &amp; Liang B &amp; Wang Y &amp; Zhao H &amp; Helgen KM &amp; Lin L &amp; Jones G &amp; Zhang S." box="[284,430,1795,1819]" journalOrPublisher="J Mammal." pageId="11" pageNumber="324" pagination="736 - 744" part="88" refId="ref17087" refString="Li G, Liang B, Wang Y, Zhao H, Helgen KM, Lin L, Jones G, Zhang S. 2007. Echolocation calls, diet, and phylogenetic relationships of Stoliczka's trident bat, Aselliscus stoliczkanus (Hipposideridae). J Mammal. 88: 736 - 744." title="Echolocation calls, diet, and phylogenetic relationships of Stoliczka's trident bat, Aselliscus stoliczkanus (Hipposideridae)" type="journal article" year="2007">Li et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Previously, 
<taxonomicName box="[575,652,1795,1819]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Coelops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[575,652,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Coelops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been grouped in a separate tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Tate (1941: 11)" authorityName="Tate" authorityPageNumber="11" authorityYear="1941" box="[427,683,1827,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Coelopidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Coelopini">
Coelopini 
<bibRefCitation author="Tate GHH" box="[534,683,1827,1851]" journalOrPublisher="A review of the genus Hipposideros with special reference to Indo-Australian species. Bull Am Mus Nat Hist." pageId="11" pageNumber="324" pagination="353 - 393" part="73" refId="ref19388" refString="Tate GHH. 1941 b. Results of the Archbold Expeditions No. 35. A review of the genus Hipposideros with special reference to Indo-Australian species. Bull Am Mus Nat Hist. 73: 353 - 393." title="Results of the Archbold Expeditions" type="journal article" year="1941">Tate (1941:11)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(sensu; 
<bibRefCitation author="McKenna MC &amp; Bell SK" box="[135,431,1859,1883]" journalOrPublisher="New York: Columbia University Press" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" refId="ref17407" refString="McKenna MC, Bell SK. 1997. Classification of mammals. New York: Columbia University Press." title="Classification of mammals" type="book" year="1997">McKenna and Bell [1997]</bibRefCitation>
= Coelopinae 
<bibRefCitation author="Tate GHH" box="[590,752,1859,1883]" journalOrPublisher="A review of the genus Hipposideros with special reference to Indo-Australian species. Bull Am Mus Nat Hist." pageId="11" pageNumber="324" pagination="353 - 393" part="73" refId="ref19388" refString="Tate GHH. 1941 b. Results of the Archbold Expeditions No. 35. A review of the genus Hipposideros with special reference to Indo-Australian species. Bull Am Mus Nat Hist. 73: 353 - 393." title="Results of the Archbold Expeditions" type="journal article" year="1941">Tate [1941:11]</bibRefCitation>
), which comprised 
<taxonomicName box="[334,411,1891,1915]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Coelops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[334,411,1891,1915]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Coelops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[478,604,1891,1915]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dorst" authorityYear="1947" box="[478,599,1891,1915]" genus="Paracoelops" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" rank="genus">Paracoelops</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the latter no longer recognized as a valid genus (Thong, Dietz, et al. 2012). Our findings provide strong support for the sister taxa relationship between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1941" box="[1109,1202,137,161]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Aselliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1109,1202,137,161]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Aselliscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1263,1340,137,161]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Coelops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1263,1340,137,161]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="324">Coelops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recovered by 
<bibRefCitation author="Li G &amp; Liang B &amp; Wang Y &amp; Zhao H &amp; Helgen KM &amp; Lin L &amp; Jones G &amp; Zhang S." box="[857,1005,169,193]" journalOrPublisher="J Mammal." pageId="11" pageNumber="324" pagination="736 - 744" part="88" refId="ref17087" refString="Li G, Liang B, Wang Y, Zhao H, Helgen KM, Lin L, Jones G, Zhang S. 2007. Echolocation calls, diet, and phylogenetic relationships of Stoliczka's trident bat, Aselliscus stoliczkanus (Hipposideridae). J Mammal. 88: 736 - 744." title="Echolocation calls, diet, and phylogenetic relationships of Stoliczka's trident bat, Aselliscus stoliczkanus (Hipposideridae)" type="journal article" year="2007">Li et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
